title.narrative: Cote d'Ivoire - Emergency Infrastructure Renewal Project

description.narrative: The objective of the project is to improve access to basic infrastructure in targeted urban and rural areas, and, in the event of an Eligible Crisis or Emergency, to provide immediate and effective response to said Eligible Crisis or Emergency.

condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Article V.5.01. (a) | Description :The Project Management Contract has been duly executed, on terms andconditions acceptable to the Association, between the Recipient and the Project Coordination Unit of the Emergency InfrastructureRenewal Project (PCU-EIRP). | Due Date :15-Oct-2012

Finance Agreement :Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 / Section I / A. 2 (b) | Description :For the duration of the Project, thePCU-PRICI shall maintain a team including a financial management assistant, an environmental safeguards specialist, a socialsafeguard specialist, a coordinator, and a municipal development specialist, all of whom shall have qualifications and experienceacceptable to the Association. | Due Date :27-Jan-2017

Finance Agreement :Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 / Section V / B. (b) | Description :The Recipient shall deposit, into theCounterpart Funds Account an amount corresponding to one fourth of the Recipient’s share of the cost of the Annual Work Plan andBudget for each Fiscal Year as set forth in the Financing Agreement or in accordance with such other schedule as may be agreed fromtime to time between the Recipient and the Association. | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 / Section I / A. 3 | Description :The Recipient shall, no later than two (2) months after theEffective Date, recruit a municipal development specialist, an environmental safeguards specialist and a social safeguardsspecialist under terms of reference and with the qualification and experience satisfactory to the Association. | Due Date:28-Dec-2016

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 / Section I / A. 3 | Description :The Recipient shall, no later than two (2) months after theEffective Date, recruit a municipal development specialist, an environmental safeguards specialist and a social safeguardsspecialist under terms of reference and with the qualification and experience satisfactory to the Association. | Due Date:28-Dec-2016

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 / Section I / B. 2 | Description :The Recipient shall, throughout Project implementation, maintain orconclude, not later than one month after the Effective Date, as the case may be, Delegated Management Contracts on terms andconditions acceptable to the Association, with each of the Implementing Agencies. | Due Date :28-Nov-2016

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 / Section I / B. 3(a) | Description :Not later than eighteen (18) months after the Effective Date,undertake, in conjunction with the Association, a mid-term review of the Project (the “Mid-term Review”), covering the progressachieved in the implementation of the Project | Due Date :30-Apr-2014

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 / Section I / B. 3(b) | Description :Not less than three (3) months prior to the beginning of theMid-term Review, prepare under terms of reference satisfactory to the Association, and furnish to the Association, a reportintegrating the results of the monitoring and evaluation activities performed pursuant to this Agreement on the progress achieved |Due Date :31-Jan-2014

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 / Section I / C. 1 | Description :The Recipient shall, not later than two (2) months after theEffective Date, update the Project Implementation Manual in a manner satisfactory to the Association, to reflect the specificcontent and design of the Project and ensure consistency with its objective. | Due Date :28-Dec-2016

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 / Section I / D. 1 (a) | Description :The Recipient shall, prepare and adopt an Environmental andSocial Management Framework (ESMF) and a Resettlement Policy Framework (RPF), both of which shall be acceptable to the Associationand fully compliant with the Association’s social and environmental policies, taking steps as needed to ensure that they are bothduly disclosed and made publicly available for public consultations. | Due Date :15-Jan-2013

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 / Section V / A. 1 (b) | Description :The Recipient shall not later than the last day of everyquarter, beginning in the 1st quarter of FY17, deposit into the Counterpart Funds Account an amount corresponding to one fourth ofthe Recipient's share of the cost of the Annual Work Plan and Budget for that Fiscal Year as set forth in the Financing Agreementor in accordance with such other schedule as may be agreed | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 / Section V / A. 1 (b) | Description :The Recipient shall not later than the last day of everyquarter, beginning in the 1st quarter of FY17, deposit into the Counterpart Funds Account an amount corresponding to one fourth ofthe Recipient's share of the cost of the Annual Work Plan and Budget for that Fiscal Year | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 /C.1 | Description :The Recipient shall, not later than two (2) months after the Effective Date,update the Project Implementation Manual in a manner satisfactory to the Association, to reflect the specific content and design ofthe Project and ensure consistency with its objective. | Due Date :28-Dec-2016
